<h2 id=3D"1">opam 2.5.2</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-1">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-opam-2-5-2/18338/1">htt=
ps://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-opam-2-5-2/18338/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orga0c8ba0" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"orga0c8ba0">Kate announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-orga0c8ba0">
<p>
Hi everyone,
</p>

<p>
opam 2.5.2 is now available. This release is fixing:
</p>
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>a security issue (<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/security-advisori=
es/blob/main/advisories/2026/OSEC-2026-10.md">OSEC-2026-10</a>)</li>
<li>a regression from 2.5.1 preventing cross-compiled packages that use dun=
e from installing properly (<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/dune/issues=
/14393">ocaml/dune#14393</a>)</li>
</ul>

<p>
We invite everyone to upgrade to 2.5.2 as soon as possible.
</p>

<p>
If you depend on the older opam package of your preferred distribution, mai=
ntainers of distributions such as Debian Stable have been notified and we e=
xpect backporting of the relevant fixes to be available there very soon.
</p>

<p>
You can read our <a href=3D"https://opam.ocaml.org/blog/opam-2-5-2/">blog p=
ost</a> for relevant links and details.
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org3e3abfe" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org3e3abfe">Try it!</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org3e3abfe">
<p>
The upgrade instructions are unchanged:
</p>

<p>
For Unix systems
</p>
<pre class=3D"example" id=3D"org99e6be0">
bash -c "sh &lt;(curl -fsSL https://opam.ocaml.org/install.sh) --version 2.=
5.2"
</pre>
<p>
or from PowerShell for Windows systems
</p>
<pre class=3D"example" id=3D"org62db0d8">
Invoke-Expression "&amp; { $(Invoke-RestMethod https://opam.ocaml.org/insta=
ll.ps1) } -Version 2.5.2"
</pre>
<p>
Please report any issues to the <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/opam/is=
sues">bug-tracker</a>.
</p>

<p>
Happy hacking,
&lt;&gt; &lt;&gt; The opam team &lt;&gt; &lt;&gt; :camel:
</p>
</div>
